Students solve problems of choice and development of materials. They collect and analyze data about availability, properties and design options of materials necessary for given applications, and propose solutions to the problems of choice and design of materials.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is development of the skills of students to solve problems in materials design, and to give supplementary knowledge about technological and structural materials, their properties, technologies and applications.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course a student has systematic overview and broad-based knowledge about modern technological and structural materials, their properties, technologies and applications. He/she  is able to participate in reasearch of materials, can gather, analyze and present the results.
